{
  "texts": [
    "This means that there is no true corrective action for any maintenance problem and that corrective actions can vary based on several factors.",
    "These factors can be related to the operator, the maintenance task, time spent inspecting the problem, tools available to inspect the problem, and any other additional context.",
    "Table 4 in Appendix shows additional instances of new maintenance problems with syntactically and semantically similar existing problems along with the corresponding corrective actions.",
    "Note the problem low compression observed on cyl #4.",
    "It has been semantically matched to the existing problem low compression on cylinder 3 (55) twice, but they both suggest different corrective actions."
  ]
}